TITLE: "U.S. pair of Chock and Bates win first world ice dance title"
DESCRIPTION: Madison Chock and Evan Bates of the United States won their first ice dance title at the figure skating world championships on Saturday.

TITLE: "Houston Methodist patient's brain tumor shrinks after using experimental helmet for 6 months"
AUTHOR: Mayra Moreno
DESCRIPTION: Last October, we first told you about a woman with a deadly brain tumor undergoing an experimental treatment. ABC13's Mayra Moreno checked in on her, and her results are astonishing.

TITLE: "Allergy Season Is Getting Worse And Lasting Longer. Here's What Doctors Want You To Know."
DESCRIPTION: Your seasonal allergies are likely to get more intense, but you can take steps to prepare.

TITLE: "Why don’t we have vaccines for fungal infections?"
AUTHOR: Keren Landman

TITLE: "Tulane receives up to $16 million to move nasal pneumonia vaccine from the lab to clinical trials"
DESCRIPTION: The National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases awarded an up to $16 million contract to Tulane University to bring to phase one clinical trial a nasal spray vaccine university researchers invented to thwart antibiotic-resistant Klebsiella pneumoniae, a leading cause of pneumonia.

TITLE: "TTUHSC El Paso scientist receives $2.6 million NIH grant for research on tuberculosis"
DESCRIPTION: For over a century, El Paso has long been a sanctuary for individuals suffering from tuberculosis. It will soon be home to groundbreaking research that prevents the debilitating disease.

TITLE: "LA County’s 3-year COVID Emergency Ends On March 31. Here’s What Will Change"
DESCRIPTION: Rent protections are among the emergency orders that will expire.

TITLE: "Substance use disorders not associated with COVID-19-related mortality"
DESCRIPTION: New research from Boston Medical Center found that substance use disorders do not increase the likelihood of dying from COVID-19.

TITLE: "Obamacare at 13: Biden and a KHN reporter remember"
DESCRIPTION: I was back in the crowded East Room of the White House on Thursday, as I was 13 years ago, this time standing under a portrait of first first lady Martha Washington, when President Joe Biden entered for a lunchtime event focused on the Affordable Care Act.
